        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:50AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1250 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles south of Ephesus to 8 miles south of
Franklin to near Lagrange. Movement was west at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Valley, Lanett, Roanoke, Wedowee, Lake Wedowee, Stroud, Lakeview,
Five Points, Malone, Post Oak Forks, Denson, River View, Amity Park,
Standing Rock, Welch, Fredonia, Veasey Creek Park, Huguley, Fairfax,
and Crystal Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
east central Alabama.</instruction>
